headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 33 points and 16 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers won their seventh straight game and handed Detroit its seventh loss in a row, beating the Pistons 114-106 on Friday night in an NBA In-Season Tournament opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid has 33 points and 16 rebounds, 76ers beat Pistons 114-106 for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward scored 27 points, LaMelo Ball added 25 and the Charlotte Hornets shook off their 3-point shooting struggles just in time to earn a 124-117 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayward, Ball lead late Hornets surge past Wizards in their NBA In-Season Tournament debut

headlines.description: — Celtics coach Joe Mazzulla didn’t have any extra discussion with his team about its first In-Season Tournament game. It was just 1 of 82 games as far as he was concerned.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown scores 28 points, Celtics hit 19 3s and beat Nets 121-107 in NBA tournament play

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 25 points, Alperen Sengun added 24 and the Houston Rockets stretched their winning streak to five with a 104-101 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets win fifth straight game, beat Pelicans 104-101 in NBA In-Season Tournament debut

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen and Jordan Clarkson each scored 26 points and the Utah Jazz held off the Memphis Grizzlies 127-121 on Friday night in the NBA In-Season Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, Clarkson each score 26 points, Jazz hold off Grizzlies 127-121

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Timberwolves with impressed with Victor Wembanyama, which made their victory that much more satisfying.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Timberwolves hold off Wembanyama, Spurs 117-110 in tournament opener for fifth straight win

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 44 points and the Dallas Mavericks routed the Los Angeles Clippers 144-126 on Friday night in an NBA In-Season Tournament game, the Clippers’ third straight loss since James Harden joined the lineup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 44 points in Mavericks' 144-126 tournament win over Clippers

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — LeBron James looked liked an aging veteran for a few seconds Friday night, limping around the baseline and grabbing at his lower left leg after getting fouled during the first quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 32 points, Lakers rally to beat Suns 122-119 to snap 3-game skid

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 17 points, 13 assists and 12 rebounds to move into sole possession of second place on the Kings’ career list for triple-doubles, leading Sacramento to a 105-98 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder in an In-Season Tournament...
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis gets 15th triple-double with Sacramento, Kings beat Thunder in the In-Season Tournament
